column2: She is a liar and disgusting.  SHE IS AN ABUSER.  There is nothing about that face that is beautiful. It represents pure evil
column44: Remove Amber Heard from L’Oréal Paris
column51: Remove Amber Heard from L’Oréal Paris
column52:
Amber Heard was caught multiple times lying on the stand to cover her own actions against Johnny Depp. L’Oréal Paris (Women’s Cosmetic Line) still employs, and uses Mrs. Heard as “Spokesperson” even calling her Heroine of our time, in better words.

Mrs. Heard has given drastic, vile and awful pictures of allegations that happened with no proof, and set a horrible example for the Women, and Men who have been actual victims of abuse. 

Remove Amber Heard for L’Oréal Paris.

 

We the People have the right, and free speech to voice our opinions, and speak up to Big Company’s to remove shameful public figures, as it represents Victims poorly, And the brand poorly.

column2: As an ACTUAL victim of SA & DV it makes me sick that your front runner is a known abuser. You’re assisting in keeping our voices suppressed by allowing an abuser to flaunt her bloodied knuckles (from beating JD) during YOUR event, for the entire world to see! You’re not “empowering” women. You’re showing us survivors what you really think of us. You’re pushing us further into the shadows. You’re robbing us of our voices. As far as I’m concerned, your products are as good as the gift Amber left in JD’s bed, until you remove the abusers power from your brand and ALL of your sister brands. You make me sick.
